<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="823" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/30253:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-21">July 21,
                                1943</date>.<lb/>[Received July 21—3:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1894. I have received following telegram from Archbishop of Toledo who is
                            Primate of Spain:<note n="35" xml:id="d823fn35">Archbishop Enrique Pla y
                                Deniel.</note>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“I beg you to transmit to His Excellency the President of the
                                    United States the deep emotion of the Spanish Catholic
                                    Episcopacy and people over the bombardment of Rome,<note n="36" xml:id="d823fn36">On July 19 certain military objectives at
                                        Rome had been bombed by American planes.</note> asking that
                                    a repetition which might endanger sacred places and venerated
                                    monuments be avoided.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Please inform me promptly what reply I should make.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>